From: Anders Roxell <anders.roxell@linaro.org>
Date: Tue, 4 Sep 2018 12:47:21 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] selftests: add headers_install to lib.mk
References: bnc#1012628
Patch-mainline: 4.18.15
Git-commit: b2d35fa5fc80c27e868e393dcab4c94a0d71737f

[ Upstream commit b2d35fa5fc80c27e868e393dcab4c94a0d71737f ]

If the kernel headers aren't installed we can't build all the tests.
Add a new make target rule 'khdr' in the file lib.mk to generate the
kernel headers and that gets include for every test-dir Makefile that
includes lib.mk If the testdir in turn have its own sub-dirs the
top_srcdir needs to be set to the linux-rootdir to be able to generate
the kernel headers.

